import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    source_counts = data['source'].value_counts()
    target_counts = data['target'].value_counts()
    fig, ax1 = plt.subplots()
    ax1.bar(source_counts.index, source_counts.values, color='b')
    ax1.set_xlabel('Source')
    ax1.set_ylabel('Count', color='b')
    ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='b')
    ax2 = ax1.twinx()
    ax2.bar(target_counts.index, target_counts.values, color='r')
    ax2.set_ylabel('Count', color='r')
    ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelcolor='r')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of source and target in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(['Source', 'Target'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['source', 'target']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    pivot_data = data.pivot(index='source', columns='target', values='count')
    sns.heatmap(pivot_data, cmap='Blues', annot=True, fmt='d')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the most common source and target combination in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('source').agg({'target': 'count'})
    data = data.reset_index()
    avg_targets = data['target'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    ax.bar(data['source'], data['target'])
    ax.axhline(avg_targets, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average number of targets per source: {avg_targets:.2f}')
    ax.set_xlabel('Source')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Targets')
    ax.set_title('What is the average number of targets per source in the dataset?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
from matplotlib_venn import venn2

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sources = set(data['source'])
    targets = set(data['target'])
    venn2([sources, targets], set_colors=('#4e79a7', '#f28e2b'), set_labels=('Sources', 'Targets'))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique sources and targets in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
